{
  "doc_id": "27963",
  "text": "183-185 DMP696, SSR125543, and R278995/CRA0450 are examples of other CRF1 antagonists that have been developed which also have antidepressant-like activity reported in preclinical rodent models, helping to further support the proof of concept for this mechanism of action. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Despite the preclinical picture for CRF1 antagonism as a novel mechanism of action for antidepressant development, only one compound to date, R121919 (Janssen), has demonstrated antidepressant efficacy in clinical trials. [CITATION_3] Unfortunately, clinical development of this compound was ultimately discontinued (believed to be because of hepatotoxicity), and the initial report was never confirmed in larger studies. This has left the field to wait for the outcome of clinical evaluation of the numerous other CRF1 antagonists that have undergone development as antidepressants.",
